HEADWORD: Freshman
<hw>Fresh"man</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Freshmen</plw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>.</plu> <def>A novice; one in the
rudiments of knowledge; especially, a student during his first year in a
high school, college, or university.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> frosh.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He drank his glass and cracked his joke,⟦br⟧
And <qex>freshmen</qex> wondered as he spoke.</q>
<rj><qau>Goldsmith.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Freshman class</b></col>, <cd>the lowest of the four
classes in an American college.</cd> <mark>[ U. S.]</mark></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Freshmanship</ent>⟦br⟧
